{"parse":{"title":"Hong Kong Centre for Christian Apologetics","pageid":55971689,"revid":846998681,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Hong Kong Centre for Christian Apologetics</caption><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Founded</th><td class=\"note\">\n2017</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Type</th><td>\nNon-profit</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Focus</th><td>\nPromote <a href=\"/wiki/Christian_apologetics\" title=\"Christian apologetics\">Christian apologetics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Location</th><td class=\"label\">\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><span class=\"locality\"><a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong\" title=\"Hong Kong\">Hong Kong</a></span></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Key people</div></th><td>\nAndrew Loke (Chairman), Kai-man Kwan, Chan Man Ho, Chai Kan Yan, <a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Lam\" title=\"Stephen Lam\">Stephen Lam</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Website</th><td>\n<span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hkcca.org/\">hkcca<wbr />.org</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Hong Kong Centre for Christian Apologetics</b> (commonly referred to as <b>HKCCA</b>) is a Christian educational institution founded in 2017 by a group of professors, lecturers and businessmen in Hong Kong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The centre offers certificate courses on Christian Apologetics <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and also promotes apologetic events hosting prominent apologists.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The committee includes professors such as Chan Man Ho of the <a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_University_of_Hong_Kong\" title=\"Chinese University of Hong Kong\">Chinese University of Hong Kong</a>, Chai Kan Yan of the <a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong_Polytechnic_University\" title=\"Hong Kong Polytechnic University\">Hong Kong Polytechnic University</a>, Andrew Loke and Kai-man Kwan of <a href=\"/wiki/Hong_Kong_Baptist_University\" title=\"Hong Kong Baptist University\">Hong Kong Baptist University</a>,\nand ministers and businessmen such as Jonathan Johnson and KY Wong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The advisory has members such as <a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Lam\" title=\"Stephen Lam\">Stephen Lam</a>, formerly  Chief Secretary of the Hong Kong Government in 2011-2012, and Christian apologist and founder of <a href=\"/wiki/Reasonable_Faith\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reasonable Faith\">Reasonable Faith</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/William_Lane_Craig\" title=\"William Lane Craig\">William Lane Craig</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Hong_Kong_Centre_for_Christian_Apologetics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.epsociety.org/events/news.asp?pid=321&amp;mode=detail\">\"Evangelical Philosophical Society News\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">5 December</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Evangelical+Philosophical+Society+News&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.epsociety.org%2Fevents%2Fnews.asp%3Fpid%3D321%26mode%3Ddetail&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHong+Kong+Centre+for+Christian+Apologetics\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://hkcca.org/on-guard-course-september-2016/\">\"Certificate in Christian Apologetics (9 weeks part time course)\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">4 December</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Certificate+in+Christian+Apologetics+%289+weeks+part+time+course%29&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fhkcca.org%2Fon-guard-course-september-2016%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHong+Kong+Centre+for+Christian+Apologetics\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.icahk.org/ica-academy-te-cca/\">\"ICA Academy and HKCCA jointly offer the Apologetic course\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">4 December</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&a